---
import FenceBlock from "../components/FenceBlock.astro";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const SITE = "https://mysecondcountry.com";
const canonical = `${SITE}/privacy`;
const title = "Privacy | My Second Country";
const description =
  "Privacy notice for My Second Country, including what information the site collects, why it is used, and how to contact the operator.";
---

<Base title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <article class="corridor-page legal-page">
    <nav class="corridor-breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span aria-current="page">Privacy</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="corridor-hero">
      <p class="corridor-kicker">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="corridor-title">Privacy.</h1>
      <p class="corridor-lead">
        My Second Country is a public relocation-screening site. This notice describes the
        limited information the site collects, the processors involved, and the launch gates
        that must be complete before email collection or payment flows are used.
      </p>
    </header>

    <FenceBlock />

    <section class="corridor-section" aria-labelledby="privacy-operator">
      <div class="corridor-section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="corridor-kicker">Operator</p>
          <h2 id="privacy-operator">Who controls the site</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="corridor-section-note">
          The legal entity name is pending founder confirmation before public promotion or email collection.
          Contact hello@mysecondcountry.com for privacy questions or requests.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="corridor-section" aria-labelledby="privacy-data">
      <div class="corridor-section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="corridor-kicker">Data</p>
          <h2 id="privacy-data">What is collected</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="corridor-section-note">
          The site is designed to collect the smallest useful record for product quality,
          source auditing, contact, and future opt-in services.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="corridor-grid">
        <section class="corridor-card">
          <span class="corridor-card__meta">Analytics</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="corridor-card__title">Plausible analytics</h3>
            <p class="corridor-card__copy">
              Plausible records cookieless page and event data, including page views,
              cited-source clicks, and product quality signals. This is used to understand
              which public pages and source trails are useful.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="corridor-card">
          <span class="corridor-card__meta">Hosting</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="corridor-card__title">Vercel hosting</h3>
            <p class="corridor-card__copy">
              Vercel serves the site and may process technical request logs needed to keep
              the site available, secure, and working.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="corridor-card">
          <span class="corridor-card__meta">Forms</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="corridor-card__title">Information you submit</h3>
            <p class="corridor-card__copy">
              If contact, screener, waitlist, or email forms are enabled, the information
              entered in the form is used only for the purpose stated near that form.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="corridor-section" aria-labelledby="privacy-processors">
      <div class="corridor-section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="corridor-kicker">Processors</p>
          <h2 id="privacy-processors">Services used</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="corridor-section-note">
          Plausible and Vercel are part of the public site. Resend is used only if email
          capture is enabled with double opt-in. Stripe is used only if a checkout or paid
          dossier flow is enabled. DPAs and transfer mechanisms must be confirmed before
          email collection or paid checkout is promoted.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="corridor-section" aria-labelledby="privacy-basis">
      <div class="corridor-section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="corridor-kicker">Basis</p>
          <h2 id="privacy-basis">Why data is used</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="corridor-section-note">
          Analytics and technical logs are used for site operation, security, and product
          quality. Contact and email data are used by consent or to respond to a request.
          Payment records, if enabled, are used to complete the transaction and meet legal
          accounting duties.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="corridor-section" aria-labelledby="privacy-retention">
      <div class="corridor-section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="corridor-kicker">Retention</p>
          <h2 id="privacy-retention">How long records are kept</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="corridor-section-note">
          Aggregated analytics are kept for trend review. Contact messages are kept only as
          long as needed to answer and maintain a basic record. Consent records for email,
          if enabled, are kept while subscribed and for a complaint-defense period after
          unsubscribe. Payment records, if enabled, follow tax and accounting retention
          rules.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="corridor-section" aria-labelledby="privacy-rights">
      <div class="corridor-section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="corridor-kicker">Rights</p>
          <h2 id="privacy-rights">Your choices</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="corridor-section-note">
          Depending on where you live, you may ask to access, correct, delete, restrict, or
          export personal data, object to some uses, or withdraw consent. Send requests to
          hello@mysecondcountry.com.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Base>
